	   <tr><td colspan=2>I disagree, I think you actually get way more bang for your buck (or mana in this case) with the higher level spells (from 1 to 16 anyhow).&nbsp;&nbsp;Here is my reasoning.<br><br>First of all, you need to make sure you are comparing the same type of spells.  For example, suffocating sphere and choke are both direct damage, debuff, damage over time spells, but chaotic feedback is strictly DD (a nuke).<br><br>So, first I'll look at the suffocating sphere, choke spells:<br><br>SPHERE   10DD    -5STR    -5AGI    8DoT    20Mana<br>CHOKE    18-20DD -7-10STR -7-10AGI 60DoT   50Mana<br><br>So you get twice the DD which is nice, but the really good stuff is the STR and AGI debuff, which can also be up to twice the 'damage'.  It's hard to tell exactly how much damage this does to the MOBs or how much it saves your groupmates, but if it's me, I'd go with the maximum debuff I can get.  And there is the DoT portion of the spell.  Choke does an incredible 7.5 TIMES the DoT as Sphere, and for just over twice the mana.  If you ask me, choke is clearly superior in this race.<br><br>Ok, so what about our nukes, Chaotic Feedback and Sanity Warp.<br><br>Chaotic      43-48DD     45Mana<br>Sanity       88-95DD     75Mana<br><br>Here again I would say that Sanity Warp is the clear winner.  For less than twice the mana you get just about exactly twice the damage.<br><br>One last note to keep in mind also.  If you were to cast lots of smaller spells over just a few larger spells, it's going to eat into your med time.  I don't know how everyone else does it, but as soon as I cast my chain of spells, I immediately med up as I watch the battle in my chat box.  So if you cast smaller spells and DoTs with less duration, you are going to be interrupting that med time more often to recast.<br><br>Well, that's my take on the down and dirty.  Thanks for bringing this up as it gave me a chance to look into all my spells myself.  And BTW, all information I got for this post was found on www.castersrealm.com , an excellent EQ site as well as this one.<br><br>hope this helps,<br><br>Yizzelar 16 Erudite Chanter on Luclin<br>&lt;Circle of Radiance&gt;<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
