	   <tr><td colspan=2>Most of what you say is valid criticism of the spell line progression.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 'insight' as to the large mana increases over the lines that you appear to be missing is that chanter get the clarity line at 16, and it rarely drops from thier buff window since that day.  Mana cost on chanter spells is semi-logical in that respect.  There still is a bit of a question as to spell choice vs mana, sometimes its better to use an old spell, but I've bought 'em all.  (see haste line\ rune line \ slow \ berzerk \ mezz line for the worse offenders in mana (or reagent cost) vs effect ratio lvl 39-54, before C2 but well afer Clarity.<br><br>Valid concern, partially vindicated...hope this redeems the string<br><br>Rupert of Terris Thule <br>52 Master of Mucking with Mobs Minds<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
